-online":{"date-parts":[[1995,2,1]]}},"URL":"https://doi.org/10.1214/ss/1177010131","ISSN":["0883-4237"],"issn-type":[{"value":"0883-4237","type":"print"}],"published":{"date-parts":[[1995,2,1]]}},{"indexed":{"date-parts":[[2026,3,5]],"date-time":"2026-03-05T03:12:10Z","timestamp":1772680330833,"version":"3.50.1"},"reference-count":0,"publisher":"World Scientific Pub Co Pte Lt","issue":"01","content-domain":{"domain":[],"crossmark-restriction":false},"short-container-title":["Fractals"],"published-print":{"date-parts":[[1997,3]]},"abstract":"<jats:p> This paper addresses the question of whether self-similar processes are sufficient to model packet network traffic, or whether a broader class of multifractal processes is needed. By using the absolute moments of aggregate traffic measurements, we conclude that measured local-area network (LAN) and wide-area network (WAN) traffic traces, with the sample means subtracted, are well modeled by random processes that are either exactly or asymptotically self-similar. </jats:p>","DOI":"10.1142/s0218348x97000073","type":"journal-article","created":{"date-parts":[[2003,5,22]],"date-time":"2003-05-22T11:43:05Z","timestamp":1053603785000},"page":"63-73","source":"Crossref","is-referenced-by-count":118,"title":["Is Network Traffic Self-Similar or Multifractal?"],"prefix":"10.1142","volume":"05","author":[{"given":"Murad S.","family":"Taqqu","sequence":"first","affiliation":[{"name":"Boston University, Department of Mathematics, 111 Cummington Street, Boston, MA 02215-2411, USA"}],"role":[{"role":"author","vocabulary":"crossref"}]},{"given":"Vadim","family":"Teverovsky","sequence":"additional","affiliation":[{"name":"Boston University, Department of Mathematics, 111 Cummington Street, Boston, MA 02215-2411, USA"}],"role":[{"role":"author","vocabulary":"crossref"}]},{"given":"Walter","family":"Willinger","sequence":"additional","affiliation":[{"name":"Bellcore, Morristown, NJ 07960-6438, USA"}],"role":[{"role":"author","vocabulary":"crossref"}]}],"member":"219","published-online":{"date-parts":[[2011,11,20]]},"container-title":["Fractals"],"language":"en","link":[{"URL":"https://www.worldscientific.com/doi/pdf/10.1142/S0218348X97000073","content-type":"unspecified","content-version":"vor","intended-application":"similarity-checking"}],"deposited":{"date-parts":[[2019,8,7]],"date-time":"2019-08-07T13:15:33Z","timestamp":1565183733000},"score":44.92524,"resource":{"primary":{"URL":"https://www.worldscientific.com/doi/abs/10.1142/S0218348X97000073"}},"issued":{"date-parts":[[1997,3]]},"references-count":0,"journal-issue":{"issue":"01","published-online":{"date-parts":[[2011,11,20]]},"published-print":{"date-parts":[[1997,3]]}},"alternative-id":["10.1142/S0218348X97000073"],"URL":"https://doi.org/10.1142/s0218348x97000073","ISSN":["0218-348X","1793-6543"],"issn-type":[{"value":"0218-348X","type":"print"},{"value":"1793-6543","type":"electronic"}],"published":{"date-parts":[[1997,3]]}},{"indexed":{"date-parts":[[2026,3,31]],"date-time":"2026-03-31T20:59:03Z","timestamp":1774990743047,"version":"3.50.1"},"reference-count":0,"publisher":"Oxford University PressOxford","isbn-type":[{"value":"9780198523994","type":"print"},{"value":"9781383024029","type":"electronic"}],"content-domain":{"domain":[],"crossmark-restriction":false},"published-print":{"date-parts":[[1996,9,5]]},"abstract":"<jats:title>Abstract</jats:title>\n               <jats:p>This paper provides a bibliographical guide to researchers and traffic engineers who are interested in self-similar traffic modeling and analysis. It lists some of the most recent network traffic studies and includes surveys and research papers in the areas of data analysis, statistical inference, mathematical modeling, queueing and performance analysis. It also contains references to other areas of applications (e.g., hydrology, economics, geophysics, biology and biophysics) where similar developments have taken place and where numerous results have been obtained that can often be directly applied in the network traffic context. Heavy-tailed distributions, their relation to self-similar modeling, and corresponding estimation techniques are also covered in this guide.</jats:p>","DOI":"10.1093/oso/9780198523994.003.0020","type":"book-chapter","created":{"date-parts":[[2023,11,3]],"date-time":"2023-11-03T09:01:31Z","timestamp":1699002091000},"page":"339-344","source":"Crossref","is-referenced-by-count":76,"title":["A bibliographical guide to self-similar traffic and performance modeling for modern high-speed networks"],"prefix":"10.1093","author":[{"given":"Walter","family":"Willinger","sequence":"first","affiliation":[],"role":[{"role":"author","vocabulary":"crossref"}]},{"given":"Murad S","family":"Taqqu","sequence":"additional","affiliation":[],"role":[{"role":"author","vocabulary":"crossref"}]},{"given":"Ashok","family":"Erramilli","sequence":"additional","affiliation":[],"role":[{"role":"author","vocabulary":"crossref"}]}],"member":"286","container-title":["Stochastic Networks Theory and Applications"],"language":"en","link":[{"URL":"https://academic.oup.com/book/chapter-pdf/52356793/isbn-9780198523994-book-part-20.pdf","content-type":"unspecified","content-version":"vor","intended-application":"similarity-checking"}],"deposited":{"date-parts":[[2023,11,3]],"date-time":"2023-11-03T09:03:03Z","timestamp":1699002183000},"score":41.299973,"resource":{"primary":{"URL":"https://academic.oup.com/book/53063/chapter/421970820"}},"issued":{"date-parts":[[1996,9,5]]},"ISBN":["9780198523994","9781383024029"],"references-count":0,"URL":"https://doi.org/10.1093/oso/9780198523994.003.0020","published":{"date-parts":[[1996,9,5]]}}],"items-per-page":3,"query":{"start-index":0,"search-terms":null}}}